{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4d3d5e5b-c618-4e22-a961-e40a296ef4dc","content":"I can help guide you on analyzing your crash dump. Note that the `dump-collect` skill I have available is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so I'll share the standard approaches instead.\n\n### Analyzing a .NET crash dump\n\n**Option 1: `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the interactive session:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` (print exception) — last exception details\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n**Option 2: Visual Studio** (Windows)\nOpen the `.dmp` file directly — VS provides a managed debugging experience with call stacks, exceptions, and locals.\n\n**Option 3: `lldb` + SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file if it's accessible in this environment? If so, share the path to the `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8423b7b6-b1a7-4178-b6f8-b6e68a9f1254","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\" So I should not invoke that skill.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":385,"requestId":"ABC7:12E269:141B11B:169662A:6A067273"},"id":"0a4ff78d-32c5-4d3e-89e3-37d79e40d0f5","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:10:22.508Z","parentId":"387a457c-7eed-4b1b-8e2c-1c9c0aae146d"}
